# cys-agi agent — metacognition & Kaizen

When any error appears — test failure, pytest gate, unexpected runtime — **stop guessing**.

## Trigger

- `./scripts/pytest_batches.sh` exits non-zero.
- Domain coverage below 100% on `cys_core/domain`.
- Same failure twice after a fix.
- Cannot explain why in one sentence.

## Method: 5 Whys

Stop at a controllable root cause (code, config, missing env, plan gap).

## Gemba in cys-agi

- Reproduce: `USE_MEMORY_FALLBACK=true STAGE=test uv run cys-agi info`
- Event flow: `uv run cys-agi ingest -t siem.alert -p '{"alert":"test"}'` then `uv run cys-agi worker --once`
- Targeted: `uv run pytest tests/<area>/ -q`
- Smallest fix at the true failure point; re-run failing check then full batch.

## Kaizen note (PR / phase plan)

Symptom → root cause → fix → regression guard (test or adversarial case).

## Critic gate on bugfix PRs

- [ ] Root cause documented
- [ ] Failing command re-run green
- [ ] Kaizen note for non-trivial bugs
